Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Supervisor, Programs NEWMARKET , ON Description Overview of position Under the direction of the Manager, Programs &amp; Community Engagement, the Supervisor, Programs is responsible for the management and implementation of all library programming for Newmarket Public Library. Ensures the evaluation and oversight of all library programs and ensures the provision of diverse and varied programming for the community for people of all ages. The Supervisor, Programs is also responsible for supporting the library’s social media and the marketing of the library’s programs and services. Oversees all Xplor functionality and the creation of program content for the library’s social media and promotional tools. Credentials Completion of Master of Information Studies or Library and Information Technician with 3-5 years of progressive experience in a supervisory level or an equivalent combination of education and experience.Proficient in the use of MS Office (e.g., Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook), Access and internet applications.Class G Driver’s license in good standing is an asset. Knowledge/Skills Required Experience in a non-profit environment, community organizing, event planning, community advocate or recreation environment Library knowledge, experience and education is an asset.Previous sound experience in programming, marketing and social media, public speaking, and community engagement.Knowledge of program planning and community engagement processes.Experience supervising in a unionized environment. Project management knowledge is an asset.Demonstrated knowledge of staff supervision and development, team building, and conflict resolution. Strong customer service skills with an ability to maintain composure regardless of the demands of the environment.Strong, interpersonal, consultative, organizational, problem-solving, analytical and presentation skills. Excellent verbal and written communication skills.Thorough knowledge of community development, and networking skills to develop partnerships with service clubs, not for profit, community organizations and private business partners. Strong demonstrated knowledge of special events encompassing a wide range of community needs, emerging trends, and innovative opportunities.Knowledge of procurement practices, policies, and procedures., as well as financial monitoring to work within budgeted resources. Experience in budget preparation and management of a budget.Sound knowledge in research, statistics, and trend analysis.Demonstrated experience with social media content creation.Ability to work a flexible work week (including evenings and weekends) when required.Knowledge of applicable legislation, bylaws, and the ability to interpret legislation such as Accessibility for Ontarians with Disability Act (AODA), Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act (MFIPPA), Vital Statistics Act, Occupational Health, and Safety Act, Employment Standards Act and administrative bylaws. Hours of work 35 hours a week including evening and weekend shifts How to apply Submit a cover letter and resume to https://newmarket.hua.hrsmart.com/hr/ats/Posting/view/2501 We thank all applicants for their interest. However, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Newmarket Public Library is committed to accommodating all applicants in accordance with the Ontario Human Rights Code for all employment activities including the recruitment process. The Newmarket Public Library is committed to a barrier-free recruitment and selection process. We uphold our values of diversity, equity, inclusion and anti-racism in the delivery of our services and in our workplace. The Library encourages applications from all applicants, including members of groups with historical employment barriers to equity, this is including but not limited to, Indigenous, Black and Racialized Groups, People with Disabilities, Women and Persons within the 2SLGBTQ+ community. Compensation $87,947 - $104,699 Closes: 7 October, 2024 Newmarket Public Library NEWMARKET , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
