Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician 3 - Area Lead - Squamish Campus North Vancouver , BC Description Competition Number S181230PPosition Title Library Technician 3 - Area Lead - Squamish CampusPosition Number S99653Employee Group StaffPosition Status Temporary Part-TimeStart Date 11/01/2024End Date 04/30/2025Department LibraryAdditional Notes Come join our team at Capilano University Library! We are seeking a library technician to join our team at our Squamish Campus.Location Squamish ValleyWorking with usAt Capilano University, learners are our focus. Guided by the goals outlined in Envisioning and Illuminating 2030, employees play an essential role in creating an exceptional learning experience for and with learners and are central to a thriving campus community. Together, we are inspired by imagination and Capilano University is one of the leading teaching-focused universities in British Columbia and one of BC’s Top Employers. Grounded by our sense of purpose, we offer a meaningful, friendly, and dynamic work environment.Located at CapU’s Squamish campus, the Area Lead supports CapU Library’s regional services by providing oversight and coordination of the daily operations associated with library services at the Squamish campus and collaborating on projects with the University Librarian, librarians, and technicians at the North Vancouver campus to support library services for the region.What you’ll do In addition to providing front facing support to students and faculty, overseeing borrower system functions (including inter-campus library materials) and handling student inquiries, the Area Lead will also collaborate with other Squamish employees in supporting student engagement activities and troubleshooting issues relating to student academic support. The Area Lead will also work with the Library Services Supervisor in developing procedures and processes specific to regional campus needs. We are looking for someone who will collaborate with colleagues and interact with students, faculty, and members of the community. This role will work closely with a small team at the Squamish CapU campus to provide library services that align with program development at this location. You will report to the University Librarian and receive direction from the Library Services Supervisor.What you’ll bringCompletion of a two-year Library Technology Diploma comparable to the programs offered at Langara College and the University of the Fraser Valley.Three years of related library experience, including at least two years of customer service experience.For more information For more information, please see the complete job description. For more information on the University’s vision visit Envisioning 2030 – Capilano University Take a virtual tour of our campus here: Visit CapU – Capilano UniversityBenefitsAt Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life. Take a sneak peek to see what it is like to work at Capilano University. If we could make the application process more accessible for you, or if you have any questions, please contact Christina Neigel at ChristinaNeigel@capilanou.caPosting Detail InformationDays and Hours of Work Work week: 17.5 hours per week Mon-Friday at the Squamish Capilano University Campus with hours may be subject to change. There may be occasional need to attend other CapU campuses for the purpose of training and meeting activity.Pay Group 20Salary $33.46 per hourUnion MoveUPJob Open Date 09/03/2024Job Close Date 10/31/2024Open Until Filled YesQuick Link for Posting https://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/7428 Compensation $33.46 per hour Closes: 31 October, 2024 Capilano University - Library North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
